Properties.femaleVariant: [en_us][GT]I thought I would be here first...
[en_us][GT]I was nearby.
[en_us][GT]You're coming with me?
[en_us][GT]Are you sure you want to go with me? It's just a meeting with the fixer.
[en_us][GT]What did Hands request in exchange for help?
[en_us][GT]What a fixer usually demands of you.
[en_us][GT]Just don't interfere.
[en_us][GT]Just remember that this is my backyard. Stick to the passenger seat.
[en_us][GT]Quid pro quo.
[en_us][GT]Fixers want people they can rely on to keep other people happy.
[en_us][GT]Hands?
[en_us][GT]Hello, V.
[en_us][GT]You didn't come alone.
[en_us][GT]Do not worry about it.
[en_us][GT]This is my support.
[en_us][GT]You'll do something for him, he'll do you a favor, and that's how it goes.
[en_us][GT]Now I need to talk to my guest. Please forgive us.
[en_us][GT]The cargo will be waiting at the marina, dressed up and smelling nice.
[en_us][GT]I do not like surprises.
[en_us][GT]Yes, of course.
[en_us][GT][rus] American asshole. [/ rus]
[en_us][GT]Are you coming?
[en_us][GT]It was nice.
[en_us][GT]I don't like this guy.
[en_us][GT]We come in, we talk, we leave. No spy tricks, no secret passwords, no saving presidents...
[en_us][GT]That means no spy kung fu. Don't ruing this contact for me.
[en_us][GT]Just don't get us into a situation with no way out.
[en_us][GT]Us? Doing business with Hands is my business.
[en_us][GT]You are an FIA agent at the moment. Do not forget about it.
[en_us][GT]I'm sorry, but I don't think we understood each other. It's my fault.
[en_us][GT]Yes?
[en_us][GT]The cargo will be waiting at the marina unless I change my mind for some reason.
[en_us][GT]There is no room for any surprises here. Unless something happens on your side. Should I be worried?
[en_us][GT]No, of course not.
[en_us][GT][lean back and wait]
[en_us][GT]You took your time.
[en_us][GT]I was helping Alex get the equipment we'll need later.
[en_us][GT]Betray the FIA and stuff.
[en_us][GT]Betray a few agents, denounce a spy, shoot down the presidential shuttle...
[en_us][GT]You know, stuff.
[en_us][GT]Don't mind him.
[en_us][GT]It is not that easy. Your companion seems very dangerous.
[en_us][GT]Everyone needs support from time to time.
[en_us][GT]I agree. But I thought you've been working alone since the events in Konpeki.
[en_us][GT]It depends.
[en_us][GT]Low blow, Hands.
[en_us][GT]Some tasks require more than one pair of hands.
[en_us][GT]That was low of you, Hands. Remind me of Jackie Welles' death?
[en_us][GT]It is true. For example, if I were an agent of a foreign government agency ...
[en_us][GT]I think I would seek the support of a local mercenary.
[en_us][GT]I knew him even before you started working together. Reliable man. Shame.
[en_us][GT]Of course, for me it was only a professional acquaintance.
[en_us][GT]And I lost a friend.
[en_us][GT]So I hope you and Agent Reed don't become friends.
[en_us][GT]Can we get down to business?
[en_us][GT]Business... Yes, well...
[en_us][GT]I can see that working with special agents is becoming your second nature.
[en_us][GT]Please take care of her. She had killed special agents before.
[en_us][GT]Are you talking about the GIM thing? It was Netwatch's dog that got in my way.
[en_us][GT]Are you talking about the GIM thing? That Netwatch agent knew what he was doing.
[en_us][GT]Poor Bridgette didn't stand a chance with you.
[en_us][GT]Good thing you didn't hit Bridgette and her Voodoo Boys. I know you've been considering it.
[en_us][GT]She asked for it.
[en_us][GT]Sometimes I am tempted to go back there ...
[en_us][GT]Yes, and surprisingly Mrs. Yankonovich came out alive.
[en_us][GT]It's a pity Mrs. Yankonovich didn't make it out alive. She could've still been useful to me.
[en_us][GT]The most important thing is that Mr. Anderson is doing well.
[en_us][GT]But your job was to save Mr. Anderson's life, V. Nothing else mattered.
[en_us][GT]Glad you got it done without too much bloodshed.
[en_us][GT]I was hoping Mr. Dodger would keep his head though... Oh, well.
[en_us][GT]But I don't think we understood each other. The idea was to find them and then get them out of trouble.
[en_us][GT]Congratulations on a successful action.
[en_us][GT]And did you? Because to my knowledge the hacker is still alive.
[en_us][GT]That's right. You stuck to the assignment from start to finish.
[en_us][GT]Certain things are beyond my control.
[en_us][GT]You're welcome.
[en_us][GT]Oops.
[en_us][GT]Bill and Charles aren't the sharpest tools in the shed, but I wouldn't leave them to their fate.
[en_us][GT]I thought you and Netwatch would sort it out.
[en_us][GT]A job is a job. I am not here to put value on its effects.
[en_us][GT]Methods? To hell with the methods, V! I don't like your results!
[en_us][GT]On the contrary. Methods are your forte.
[en_us][GT]It happens on this job.
[en_us][GT]I know.
[en_us][GT]I'm still alive.
[en_us][GT]In this job, you never know when the shit will hit the fan.
[en_us][GT]I prefer to hire people who can see this shit and catch it in flight BEFORE it hits the fan.
[en_us][GT]Same here. That's why I came to you.
[en_us][GT]I know, my latest record leaves a lot to be desired.
[en_us][GT]I'm still alive and I have both hands.
[en_us][GT]Understatement.
[en_us][GT]Yes... And who knows what else you will destroy with these hands.
[en_us][GT]Good to know.
[en_us][GT]But for business ... This shard has a map and information on Black Saphire.
[en_us][GT]Water under the bridge, I hope.
[en_us][GT]True, the here and now is what counts. Gigs and their results.
[en_us][GT]Do you have any problem with the way I work?
[en_us][GT]I ran errands at Anderson's clinic.
[en_us][GT]I found these cops in Dodger's Den.
[en_us][GT]Did I get the blackmailing hackers or not?
[en_us][GT]Great. Can i get it?
[en_us][GT]That's what we're here for. But I have one more small request.
[en_us][GT]I will try.
[en_us][GT]No way.
[en_us][GT]What for?
[en_us][GT]Why do you need Kurt Krausser's prints?
[en_us][GT]Let's not talk about my needs.
[en_us][GT]Alright, I'll try. But I won't force it.
[en_us][GT]No way, Hands. We had a deal and you must protect the reputation of a man who does not back down on his promises.
[en_us][GT]I'm glad.
[en_us][GT]Well said. So let us consider my offer null and void.
[en_us][GT]And one more thing ... There's this boxer, Aaron. I need some thing from the Scavs hideout at the Tech Expo.
[en_us][GT]Another gig?
[en_us][GT]I would love to see with my own eyes what the boring world of fixers and mercenaries looks like.
[en_us][GT]Seriously though, let's not waste any more time.
[en_us][GT]Okay.
[en_us][GT]Noted.
[en_us][GT]Okay. We going to see Hands now or do you wanna camp here?
[en_us][GT]Let's go.
[en_us][GT]That is?
[en_us][GT]Funny, V. Have you considered a career in comedy?
[en_us][GT]You better not get your hopes up.
[en_us][GT]What are you, now you're an art agent?
[en_us][GT]It's as if he was a death merchant. Or I don't know... an agent of a government organization.
[en_us][GT]I know, it's better not to get in your way, V.
[en_us][GT]And you know people, huh, V?
[en_us][GT]But my business suffers if you eliminate my clients, V.
[en_us][GT]Emotions rarely serve interests, V.
[en_us][GT]How's working for me working out for you, V?
[en_us][GT]I found these cops in the Dodger Den.
[en_us][GT]I got those blackmailing hackers for you, didn't I?
[en_us][GT]I arranged for you to go to the Anderson Clinic.
[en_us][GT]Never tell your fixer that, V. You'll leave a bad impression.
[en_us][GT]These Scavs use too many dirty tricks for my taste. It's good that you took care of it.
[en_us][GT]I am concerned that there has been such a misunderstanding between us. This bodes badly for the future.
[en_us][GT]Who said we didn't?
[en_us][GT]Like a hammer that drives nails. Simple, effective, predictable.
[en_us][GT]You don't like my methods?
[en_us][GT]Dead bodies and botched assignments is all you leave behind.
[en_us][GT]Wait a minute ... I have to get that.
[en_us][GT]Sweethear? Daddy's working.
[en_us][GT]Yes? Now? Okay ... So what's your problem?
[en_us][GT]Don't worry, I'll find Mr. Ball's ear as soon as I get home. Deal?
[en_us][GT]You have my word. I love you.
[en_us][GT]Sorry, business isn't everything.
[en_us][GT]What about the shard?
[en_us][GT]As I said, I still have a small request.
[en_us][GT]What request?
[en_us][GT]I thought we had a deal.
[en_us][GT]What is it about?
[en_us][GT]We've had a deal, Hands. Are you adding new terms to it?
[en_us][GT]One small handshake.
[en_us][GT]Your implant has other uses than a simple smart link.
[en_us][GT]Forget it. I won't let you fuck with my implants.
[en_us][GT]I won't even touch them.
[en_us][GT]The shard with the hotel plans also includes a program that will allow you to map fingerprints through a handshake.
[en_us][GT]And whose prints am I supposed to get for you?
[en_us][GT]Kurt Krausser. As long as you run into him in Black Saphire. Don't force it..
[en_us][GT]Business is like gears. You have to oil them regularly so that they do not jam.
[en_us][GT]At the moment, only your needs are important. For example, the Black Saphire plans.
[en_us][GT]We don't know each other that well.
[en_us][GT]We do not have to. A man who rarely shows his face only has his reputation.
[en_us][GT]Without it, he does not exist.
[en_us][GT]Here's the shard. It has everything you need to enter the hotel.
[en_us][GT]Here's the shard. Everything you need to enter the hotel and an additional program.
[en_us][GT][Take]
[en_us][GT]Thanks.
[en_us][GT]I've heard that the same Scavs are in the posession of a black box from a recently crashed shuttle...
[en_us][GT]Two birds, one stone, hmm? I'll give you Aaron's deets.
[en_us][GT]I'll see what I can do. It's all?
[en_us][GT]I'll be in touch with you soon. There is never a shortage of work here.
[en_us][GT]And ... good luck at Black Saphire.
[en_us][GT]The pleasure is all mine.
[en_us][GT]And please come back alive from the hotel.
[en_us][GT]Perhaps business is not everything, but I feel that we can still help each other in this area.
[en_us][GT]He knew who you were... That I had ties to the FIA.
[en_us][GT]And he will try to use it somehow. Or he hopes you will.
[en_us][GT]How?
[en_us][GT]I don't know, but Krausser seems to be a thorn in his side. Maybe he hopes we'll get rid of him...
[en_us][GT]Anyway, it doesn't matter now. I'll see you at Alex's as soon as you're ready.
[en_us][GT]Of course.
[en_us][GT]Good job with Hands. Just don't forget to take the shard with you.
[en_us][GT]Nice to meet you, Mr. Hands.
[en_us][db_db]Mr Hands starts to make some tea.
[en_us][db_db]Mr.Hands pulls a shard from his pocket and shows it to V before putting it away.
[en_us][db_db]Player hears a Ring Ring from hand's direction
[en_us][db_db]V Says this is rude.
[en_us][db_db]Mr.Hands waves a hand and keeps talking
